<TITLE> Mohiuddin resigns to contest CCC polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 20 (bdnews24.com)Chittagong mayor ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury resigned from his post on Thursday to allow him to contest for the mayoral post in the June 17 city corporation polls . Mohiuddin submitted his resignation letter to the chief executive officer of Chittagong City Corporation at around 10am. He has been mayor for 16 years and five months in three tenures  though he was jailed during the caretaker period. He handed over his job to panel mayor and ward councillor Zahirul Alam Dobhash. According to the law, a person cannot contest for the mayoral post whilst holding that position. Mohiuddin on Wednesday said that he would resign before filing his nomination papers on Thursday, the last date for submission. The Awami League leader is contesting for the polls as a candidate of the Citizen Committee. The current CCC tenure expires on June 25. bdn
